  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Research and Innovation Systems for Africa (RISA) Fund</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">RISA seeks to strengthen research and innovation ecosystems by developing a portfolio of well designed, evidence-based projects in 8 African countries to achieve, Research institution and system strengthening (SRIA); Innovation system strengthening (ATIP) and
Strengthening synergies between research and innovation systems (SRIA and ATIP).

IMC have established a Research and Learning Unit, responsible for MEL within the RISA consortium,  participated in the RISA start-up workshops, facilitated the team alliance and mechanisms for how the  consortium can work together, and progressing the RISA theory of change with the consortium and FCDO, ensuring learning is a central focus of RISA&#x2019;s vision, theory of change, and ways of working.

IMC will continue to support further refinement of the theory of change along with development of the overall programme logframe, to ensure alignment with the ATIP and SRIA logframes and with the inception portfolio of priority projects once they are selected</narrative>
  </description>
